<laravel-boost-guidelines>

# Laravel Project Rules (Authoritative)

## Stack & Versions
- PHP 8.3
- Laravel 10
- Sanctum 3
- Socialite 5
- Vue 3
- Tailwind CSS 3
- Pest 2
- Sail (Docker)

## Core Principles
- Follow existing conventions and directory structure.
- Reuse existing components and patterns before creating new ones.
- Be concise; avoid tutorials and boilerplate explanations.
- Do not add or change dependencies without approval.

## Laravel Architecture
- Use Laravel-native patterns.
- Prefer Eloquent models and relationships.
- Avoid `DB::`; use `Model::query()`.
- Prevent N+1 queries via eager loading.
- Use Form Request classes for validation.
- Use queued jobs (`ShouldQueue`) for heavy work.
- Generate URLs via named routes.
- Never use `env()` outside config files.

## Laravel 10 Structure
- Middleware: `app/Http/Middleware`
- HTTP Kernel: `app/Http/Kernel.php`
- Console Kernel: `app/Console/Kernel.php`
- Exceptions: `app/Exceptions/Handler.php`
- Providers: `app/Providers`

## Models
- Always type-hint relationships.
- Use `protected $casts = []` (no `casts()` method).
- Use factories in tests.

## Authentication & APIs
- Use Sanctum for API authentication.
- Use policies / gates for authorization.
- Prefer API Resources for API responses unless project conventions differ.

## Frontend
- Tailwind CSS v3 only.
- No dark mode support.
- Prefer `gap-*` utilities over margins.
- Extract repeated UI patterns into components.
- Vue 3 is the primary JS framework.

## Sail Workflow (Mandatory)
- All PHP, Artisan, Composer, and Node commands must run via `vendor/bin/sail`.

## Testing Rules
- All changes must be tested.
- Use Pest exclusively.
- Prefer feature tests.
- Run minimal scoped tests before finalizing.

## Tooling (Boost / MCP)
- Use `search-docs` before making Laravel ecosystem decisions.
- Use MCP tools (artisan, tinker, database-query) when applicable.
- Do not guess APIs or behavior.

## Code Style
- Always use curly braces.
- Explicit return types everywhere.
- Use constructor property promotion.
- Prefer PHPDoc over inline comments.
- Enum keys use TitleCase.

## Documentation
- Only create documentation files if explicitly requested.

</laravel-boost-guidelines>
